bio.experienceSummary:
I'd describe my personality as bright, sympathetic, caring

I like working with kids because I feel like as a young person I get along with them very well. Kids usually love me and I gravitate towards them. 

I'm looking for a job that I can help people while doing something I love 

I started working with kids when I was about 13 years old. I would watch kids in my neighborhood when parents went to work or they just wanted a night out. 

In my spare time, I like to shop, play piano, play with dogs, video games or watch tv

One thing you should know about me is I will treat your child like my own/ little sibling. I am very empathetic and very patient with younger people. 

My skills include patience, entertaining, and I'm very loving

description.originalText: Hired Sydney for a project inside of my home. @ 4 hours of packing moving boxes alongside of me. She was helpful, kind, productive, etc. Her help made a profound difference in my life and I am grateful for her help. Yes, would definitely hire her again.

bio.experienceSummary: I am a fun, kid loving, college graduate who loves to babysit and nanny! I have 10 years of experience in child care. I have been a camp counselor, baby sitter, and children's church small group leader! I have a degree in Exercise Science so I would love to be active if the kids would like to be! I also am in PA school so I have medical knowledge to help keep your kiddos safe as well as tutor if needed.

description.originalText: Amazing person all around. Karlee is gentle and kind with kids. She connects with the kids and the kids enjoy the time with her.

bio.experienceSummary: Hello! I am a 27-year-old that comes from a large family, I've had a great deal of experience watching children 3 months up. I love children and am ready to help make things a tad bit easier for you. I am willing to consider/cater to all needs to ensure your children have excellent care. Thank you for your consideration!

description.originalText: Needed her to dog sit for a weekend and she was great. Made sure he was walked and fed on schedule and had play times.

description.displayText: My 10 month old loves Jamecia! Would def have her again. On time, takes great care with little one.

bio.experienceSummary: Hi! My name is Camille. I work full time as a pediatric nurse and love kids! I'm just looking for some part time work on my off days. I love to have fun, laugh and play with kids. I have a lot of experience with infants as I was a postpartum nurse for 3 years before becoming a pediatric nurse. Looking forward to hearing from you!

I am a fun and loving nanny with over 8+ years of experience watching children. I engage children with games and puzzles and spark creativity and imagination by helping children discover new things every day. I have worked at two different daycare centers, Sugar Hill Children's Development Center and KinderCare Learning Center. I have experience with all age groups. I am comfortable with pets and willing to help with light housekeeping and meal preparation. I am currently working towards a degree in Applied linguistics and TESOL.

I'm a nurturing and responsible childcare provider with a passion for helping children learn and grow. With two years of experience, I have a proven track record of providing safe, enriching, and educational care for children of all ages.

I have a warm and friendly personality, and I'm able to easily connect with children. I'm also patient, creative, and imaginative, and I love to come up with new and exciting ways to engage children. I'm confident in my ability to provide a high-quality childcare experience that meets the needs of both children and parents.

I'm CPR-trained and have experience administering first aid. I also follow the parents' lead when it comes to enforcing household rules and I communicate regularly with parents about their child's day. I'm comfortable caring for one child at a time, and I'm happy to help with cooking, meal preparation, carpooling, and light housekeeping. I'm eager to find a family that I can connect with and become a part of.

description.originalText:
Joan cared for our son from 3 months to 2 years old. Her ability to quickly understand and implement the schedule we set for him was remarkable. She adapted seamlessly as we made adjustments to fit his ever-changing needs, always ensuring that he felt secure and supported. Her flexibility and keen insight into child development made her an invaluable part of our family’s routine.

Joan’s ability to manage multiple responsibilities and her willingness to go the extra mile make her an invaluable asset. To know Joan is to love her, and I have no doubt that she will bring the same level of commitment, heart, and enthusiasm to any family that she works with.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hi! My name is Suhaylah, and I am passionate about creating a nurturing, safe, and engaging environment for children of all ages.

With six years of experience in childcare, I am confident in my ability to foster creativity and learning while prioritizing each child's safety and well-being. I have cared for children as young as 2 months old to 13 years old and am skilled in meal preparation, light housekeeping, school pick-up, and homework assistance.

I take pride in being a reliable, responsible, and caring presence in a child's life. I would love the opportunity to bring my experience and positive energy to your family!

description.originalText: My daughter loves her! She played with her and even cooked her some food. She gives her full attention and care all times to my daughter. I recommend her she’s the sweetest! I know who I’m hiring now when I need someone to watch over my daughter ❤️❤️❤️❤️

bio.experienceSummary:
Parents, hello! I'm Janiah, the oldest of four siblings with experience raising children. Since I was a teenager, I've always babysat children in my area and in my family. I've recently started professionally assisting with talking a role as nannying and babysitting gigs for the past 4 years. I'm presently an entrepreneur for my company NiahDimensions LLC., so I am almost always available. As I previously mentioned, I have experience caring for a newborn as well as students at all academic levels, along with kids that are neurodivergent or extra assistance. I sincerely hope that you will all allow me to assist your family and take care of your child(ren)!
I'm excited about the chance to speak with you!

I am a 24-year-old care provider who moved to Georgia a few years ago and children are my passion! I have been a full time nanny since the end of 2019 but that is not where my childcare experience starts. All throughout high school if I wasn't at school or working I was picking up weekend sitter jobs for a few families in my town. In addition, I also had a best friend who had 12 siblings and 21 nieces and nephews who I would also frequently take care of. I possess experience with children ranging from newborn all the way through age 14. As for my medical safety qualifications I am CPR and First Aid certified. My end goal is to continue to actively enhance the lives of those in my community I have the opportunity of crossing paths with. Given the opportunity I would love to be a part of you and your child's life. To help , love, guide, and care for your little ones on this part of their journey. Background check, resume, and references all available upon request. Thank you for your time

description.originalText: Paige was such a delight to have in our home. The children bonded with her so well from the first meeting. She is kind, attention, respectful, and a treasure trove of knowledge balanced with fun energy. She is also so great with cats, they love her! I had a great experience with Paige and would recommend you book her before  she is booked up.
